    result = (Double) output;
} else if (output instanceof Boolean) {
    result = (((Boolean) output) ? 1 : 0);
}
```
Reason:
The fix involves storing the result of `expression.execute(context)` in the `output` variable and reusing it, which prevents the double computation of the expression. This ensures consistent results and improves performance by avoiding redundant evaluations.

